modelDocumentation.formattedText:
Introduction


This Model helps in calculating Net profit value for a Mining Industry. 


It has both details related Production rate, Copper Price, Copper Sold etc. 


Revenue
Revenue is derived by multiplying Copper sold, Copper Price and Conversion Rate 
Copper Price is only node which uses Simulation method as Constant 
Conversion Node has 2204.62 as constant value across all periods 
Total Cost
Total Cost is aggregation of Production, Realization and Support Service cost 
Mill throughput is formula node which considers Production Rate, Net Production Time for calculation  
C1 Cash Cost is a derived Node i.e., used to display additional information but not used in any calculation 
Posted Mining Cost is not displayed in Model i.e., its display is hidden but used to calculation in Other Node calculation
Other Nodes
Mill throughput value which is used in Revenue calculation is linked to Mill throughput of Cost branch. 
All Expense/Cost related nodes desired trend is set as Decrease 
Some of the nodes like Copper Price, Fuel Consumption Rate, Average load uses  
Weighted Average as Time Aggregation.
modelDocumentation.value:
Introduction

This Model helps in calculating Net profit value for a Mining Industry.

It has both details related Production rate, Copper Price, Copper Sold etc.

Revenue

  1. Revenue is derived by multiplying Copper sold, Copper Price and Conversion Rate
  2. Copper Price is only node which uses Simulation method as Constant
  3. Conversion Node has 2204.62 as constant value across all periods

Total Cost

  1. Total Cost is aggregation of Production, Realization and Support Service cost
  2. Mill throughput is formula node which considers Production Rate, Net Production Time for calculation
  3. C1 Cash Cost is a derived Node i.e., used to display additional information but not used in any calculation
  4. Posted Mining Cost is not displayed in Model i.e., its display is hidden but used to calculation in Other Node calculation

Other Nodes

  • Mill throughput value which is used in Revenue calculation is linked to Mill throughput of Cost branch.
  • All Expense/Cost related nodes desired trend is set as Decrease
  • Some of the nodes like Copper Price, Fuel Consumption Rate, Average load uses
  • Weighted Average as Time Aggregation.
